  "text": "Simulation is seen as a bridge to professional practice, providing authentic learning experiences under safe and controlled conditions (Kneebone et al. 2004) . In turn, expectations are that simulation can enhance performance in subsequent 'real' practices, promoting safety, quality of care, and so on [CITATION_1] . In the health context, shortage of clinical placements further fuels the deployment of simulation across the curriculum [CITATION_2] ).",
